commit.message:
Support CA certificates in PKCS#12 file (#12)

Without this change, PKCS#12 files with CA certificates might fail due to lack of the certificate chain.

Remove unneeded variable _pkcs12_password_bytes (#2, #9)

This is a left-over from the no longer existing instance variable
"self._pkcs12_password_bytes".

Remove unneeded variable _pkcs12_data (#2, #9)

This is a left-over from the no longer existing instance variable
"self._pkcs12_data".
Use the PROTOCOL_* constant with maximum compatibility

Move creation of ssl_context into init (#2, #9)

Move creation of ssl_context into init so that it only needs to happen
once.  The adapter then hands out the ssl_context from memory rather
than generating it on demand.
Improve .gitignore to ignore Python 2 and Python 3 cache files
Read project description automatically from README.md
In "make upload", create git tag only after successful upload
